    <div class="ch-body" id="body5">
      <div class="explanation-box">
        <div class="box-label">📖 Chapter Overview</div>
        <p>Depreciation = Fixed Asset ki value ka gradual decrease. Yeh ek non-cash expense hai lekin profit ko affect karta hai. CA Foundation mein SLM aur WDV dono methods se questions aate hain. Asset Account aur Provision for Depreciation Account format bhi important hai.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="topics-grid">
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>Meaning, Causes & Need for Depreciation</div>
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>SLM — Straight Line Method</div>
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>WDV — Written Down Value Method</div>
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>Change of Method & its Impact</div>
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>Revision of Estimated Useful Life</div>
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>Sale, Disposal & Exchange of Asset</div>
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>Provision for Depreciation Account</div>
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>AS-6 (Depreciation Accounting)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="formula-box">
        <div class="formula-title">📐 DEPRECIATION FORMULAS</div>
        <span class="highlight">SLM (Fixed Installment Method):</span><br>
        Annual Depreciation = (Cost − Residual Value) ÷ Useful Life<br>
        % Rate = (Annual Depreciation ÷ Cost) × 100<br><br>
        <span class="gold">WDV (Diminishing Balance Method):</span><br>
        Annual Depreciation = WDV at beginning of year × Rate%<br>
        WDV decreases every year → depreciation also decreases<br><br>
        <span class="highlight">Profit/Loss on Disposal:</span><br>
        = Sale Price − Book Value at date of sale<br>
        (Book Value = Cost − Accumulated Depreciation)
      </div>
      <div class="question-card">
        <div class="question-header" onclick="toggleQ(this)">
          <span class="q-badge">Q.1</span>
          <p>A machine was purchased on 1st April 2021 for ₹1,00,000. Useful life = 5 years. Residual value = ₹10,000. Prepare Machine Account for first 3 years using SLM. Accounts close on 31st March.</p>
          <span class="qtoggle">▼</span>
        </div>
        <div class="question-solution">
          <div class="sol-step"><div class="step-num">1</div><p>Annual Depreciation (SLM) = (₹1,00,000 − ₹10,000) ÷ 5 = <strong>₹18,000 per year</strong></p></div>
          <table class="table-simple">
            <tr><th>Year</th><th>Opening WDV</th><th>Depreciation</th><th>Closing WDV</th></tr>
            <tr><td>2021-22</td><td>₹1,00,000</td><td>₹18,000</td><td>₹82,000</td></tr>
            <tr><td>2022-23</td><td>₹82,000</td><td>₹18,000</td><td>₹64,000</td></tr>
            <tr><td>2023-24</td><td>₹64,000</td><td>₹18,000</td><td>₹46,000</td></tr>
          </table>
          <p style="margin-top:10px;background:#e3f2fd;padding:10px;border-radius:8px;"><strong>SLM Characteristic:</strong> Har saal equal depreciation = ₹18,000. WDV method mein har saal kam hoti rehti.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="exam-tip">
        <span class="et-icon">🎯</span>
        <p><strong>Exam Tip:</strong> <strong>SLM mein Depreciation Amount constant rehti hai, WDV mein percentage constant rehti hai.</strong> Asset sold ho to: Loss on Sale → Debit P&L. Profit on Sale → Credit P&L. Yeh bahut frequently poochha jaata hai!</p>
