      <div class="formula-box">
        <div class="formula-title">📐 PARTNERSHIP — KEY RATIOS & FORMULAS</div>
        <span class="highlight">Sacrificing Ratio</span> = Old Ratio − New Ratio (at time of Admission)<br>
        <span class="gold">Gaining Ratio</span>   = New Ratio − Old Ratio (at time of Retirement)<br><br>
        <span class="highlight">Goodwill Treatment (Admission):</span><br>
        New Partner brings Goodwill → Distribute to OLD partners in Sacrificing Ratio<br><br>
        <span class="gold">Revaluation A/c:</span><br>
        Dr: Decrease in Assets, Increase in Liabilities<br>
        Cr: Increase in Assets, Decrease in Liabilities<br>
        Profit/Loss transferred to partners in OLD ratio<br><br>
        <span class="highlight">Capital Method for Admission:</span><br>
        Total Capital of New Firm = New Partner's Capital × (1 ÷ New Partner's Share)<br>
        Each old partner's adjusted capital = Total Capital × Old Partner's New Share
      </div>
