          <div class="sol-step"><div class="step-num">3</div><p>Sacrificing Ratio = A : B = 1/10 : 1/10 = 1:1 (equal)</p></div>
          <div class="sol-step"><div class="step-num">4</div><p>Journal Entries:</p></div>
          <table class="table-simple">
            <tr><th>Entry</th><th>Debit</th><th>Credit</th></tr>
            <tr><td>C brings goodwill in cash</td><td>Cash A/c Dr ₹10,000</td><td>C's Capital A/c ₹10,000</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Distribute goodwill to old partners</td><td>C's Capital A/c Dr ₹10,000</td><td>A's Capital A/c ₹5,000<br>B's Capital A/c ₹5,000</td></tr>
          </table>
          <p style="margin-top:10px;background:#e8f5e9;padding:10px;border-radius:8px;font-size:13px;"><strong>Result:</strong> A gets ₹5,000 + B gets ₹5,000 (in 1:1 sacrificing ratio). C's final Goodwill entry = NIL (he brought cash, it's distributed).</p>
