    <div class="ch-body" id="body15">
      <div class="explanation-box">
        <div class="box-label">📖 Chapter Overview</div>
        <p>Accounting Ratios ek simple lekin scoring chapter hai — formulas yaad karo aur calculate karo! Yeh ratios financial health check karne ke tools hain. CA Foundation mein usually 5-8 marks ke simple calculation questions aate hain.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="topics-grid">
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>Current Ratio (Liquidity)</div>
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>Quick Ratio / Acid Test Ratio</div>
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>Debt-Equity Ratio (Solvency)</div>
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>Gross Profit Ratio (Profitability)</div>
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>Net Profit Ratio</div>
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>Return on Investment (ROI)</div>
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>Stock Turnover Ratio</div>
        <div class="topic-item"><div class="ti-dot"></div>Debtors Turnover Ratio</div>
      </div>
      <div class="formula-box">
        <div class="formula-title">📐 IMPORTANT RATIO FORMULAS</div>
        <span class="highlight">Current Ratio</span>      = Current Assets ÷ Current Liabilities   [Ideal: 2:1]<br>
        <span class="gold">Quick Ratio</span>         = (Current Assets − Stock − Prepaid) ÷ Current Liabilities   [Ideal: 1:1]<br>
        <span class="highlight">Debt-Equity Ratio</span>  = Long Term Debt ÷ Shareholders' Equity<br>
        <span class="gold">GP Ratio</span>            = (Gross Profit ÷ Net Sales) × 100<br>
        <span class="highlight">NP Ratio</span>            = (Net Profit after Tax ÷ Net Sales) × 100<br>
        <span class="gold">Stock Turnover</span>      = COGS ÷ Average Inventory (or Net Sales ÷ Avg Stock)<br>
        <span class="highlight">Debtors Turnover</span>   = Net Credit Sales ÷ Average Debtors<br>
        <span class="gold">Debtors Collection Period</span> = 365 days ÷ Debtors Turnover Ratio
      </div>
      <div class="question-card">
        <div class="question-header" onclick="toggleQ(this)">
          <span class="q-badge">Q.1</span>
          <p>From the following, calculate: (1) Current Ratio (2) Quick Ratio (3) GP Ratio. Current Assets ₹2,00,000 | Stock ₹60,000 | Current Liabilities ₹80,000 | Net Sales ₹5,00,000 | COGS ₹3,50,000</p>
          <span class="qtoggle">▼</span>
        </div>
        <div class="question-solution">
          <div class="sol-step"><div class="step-num">1</div><p><strong>Current Ratio</strong> = ₹2,00,000 ÷ ₹80,000 = <strong>2.5 : 1</strong> (Good — above ideal 2:1)</p></div>
          <div class="sol-step"><div class="step-num">2</div><p><strong>Quick Ratio</strong> = (₹2,00,000 − ₹60,000) ÷ ₹80,000 = ₹1,40,000 ÷ ₹80,000 = <strong>1.75 : 1</strong> (Very good — above 1:1)</p></div>
          <div class="sol-step"><div class="step-num">3</div><p><strong>Gross Profit</strong> = Net Sales − COGS = ₹5,00,000 − ₹3,50,000 = ₹1,50,000<br><strong>GP Ratio</strong> = (₹1,50,000 ÷ ₹5,00,000) × 100 = <strong>30%</strong></p></div>
        </div>
